country. citizens holding passports from brunei, chile, ecuador, hong kong sar (special administrative region), macau sar (special administrative region), malaysia, morocco, peru, philippines, singapore, thailand, vietnam are eligible for the visa waiver program and do not require visas to enter and remain for 30 days within indonesia. these visas cannot be extended or converted to another type of visa. [44] the airport[edit] the airport will not win any awards for style, but it is functional enough and has the usual complement of overpriced restaurants, duty-free shops and other services. atms which accept cirrus and plus cards for withdrawals are available 